Package edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_scheduler.scheduler

Class WolfScheduler

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.wolf_scheduler.scheduler.WolfScheduler
  • public class WolfScheduler
extends java.lang.Object
    WolfScheduler class is the primary class responsible for managing and and allowing the user to manipulate data related to different activities (Course and Events), as well as the schedules and catalogs that contain these activities. WolfScheduler allows the user to edit the name of the schedule, reset the schedule, add courses from the course catalog and events to schedule, and remove courses and events from the schedule. Additionally, WolfScheduler provides the functionality to view and display the activities and schedule information in the form of a 2D String array.

      • getCourseCatalog

        public java.lang.String[][] getCourseCatalog()
        Gets a 2D String array of the courses listed in the course catalog. Format: a row for each Course, 4 columns for course name, section, title, and meetingString. If no courses are in the catalog, then an empty String[][] is returned.
        Returns:
        2D String array representation of the course catalog.

      • getScheduledActivities

        public java.lang.String[][] getScheduledActivities()
        Gets 2D String array of the activities (course + event) currently in the schedule. Format: a row for each activity, 3 columns for activity name, section, and title. If no activity exists in schedule, an empty 2D String array is returned.
        Returns:
        2D String array representation of the courses listed in the schedule.

      • getFullScheduledActivities

        public java.lang.String[][] getFullScheduledActivities()
        Gets 2D String array of all of activity information from the schedule. Format: row for each activity, 7 columns for activity name, section, title, credits, instructorId, meetingDays string, and eventDetails (if applicable). If no activities are in the schedule, return an empty 2D String array.
        Returns:
        2D String array representation of the full information from a activity schedule.

      • addCourseToSchedule

        public boolean addCourseToSchedule​(java.lang.String name,
                                   java.lang.String section)
        Determines if a course already exists in course schedule using the given course name and section, if it does not then true is returned (because course can be added), otherwise false.
        Parameters:
        name - name of the course that is attempting to be added to schedule
        section - section of the course that is attempting to be added to schedule
        Returns:
        true if course can be added to schedule (DNE), false if it cannot.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - with message "You are already enrolled in [course name]" if course name already exists in schedule.

      • removeActivityFromSchedule

        Checks if a activity is removable by verifying that it exists in schedule using given activity index in schedule. If activity is in schedule, activity is removed from schedule and method returns true, otherwise return false.
        Parameters:
        idx - index of activity in schedule that is to be removed
        Returns:
        true if activity exists in schedule and activity has been removed, otherwise return false
